cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to generate code from textual descriptions of method invocations.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper addresses a problem in software development, specifically in generating code from natural language descriptions.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a self-learning approach using a large-scale code corpus to improve the accuracy of generating code from textual descriptions.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses NLP techniques and machine learning algorithms to infer the structure of method invocations from natural language descriptions.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with generating code, which is a core aspect of programming languages.
